# Automatic Dates Examples in Zolt

## Basic Date Variables

Using automatic date variables:

This document was created on: {$created}
Last modified: {$modified}

## Date Formatting

Configure global date format:

```
$date_format = "DD/MM/YYYY"
$datetime_format = "DD/MM/YYYY HH:mm"
```

### Formatted Output

**Date only:** {$created}
**Date and time:** {$datetime_format}

## Format Tokens

Available format tokens:

| Token | Description | Example |
|-------|-------------|---------|
| `DD` | Day (2 digits) | 18 |
| `MM` | Month (2 digits) | 02 |
| `YYYY` | Year (4 digits) | 2026 |
| `YY` | Year (2 digits) | 26 |
| `HH` | Hour (24h) | 14 |
| `mm` | Minutes | 30 |
| `ss` | Seconds | 45 |

## Common Date Formats

### ISO Format

```yaml
---
$date_format = "YYYY-MM-DD"
---

Created: {$created}
```

### European Format

```yaml
---
$date_format = "DD/MM/YYYY"
---

Created: {$created}
```

### US Format

```yaml
---
$date_format = "MM/DD/YYYY"
---

Created: {$created}
```

### Custom Format

```yaml
---
$date_format = "DD MMM, YYYY"
---

Created: {$created}
```

## Practical Examples

### Document Header

```yaml
---
$date_format = "DD MMMM YYYY"
---
```

# My Document

**Created:** {$created}
**Last Updated:** {$modified}

### Version History

```yaml
---
$date_format = "YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm"
---
```

## Version History

| Version | Date | Changes |
|---------|------|---------|
| 1.0.0 | {$created} | Initial release |
| 1.1.0 | {$modified} | Bug fixes and improvements |

### Blog Post

```yaml
---
$date_format = "MMMM DD, YYYY"
---
```

# Post Title

**Published:** {$created}

### Technical Report

```yaml
---
$date_format = "DD/MM/YYYY HH:mm"
$timezone = "UTC"
---
```

**Report Generated:** {$created} (UTC)

## Time Zones

### Setting Time Zone

```yaml
---
$timezone = "America/New_York"
$datetime_format = "DD/MM/YYYY HH:mm"
---

Created: {$created}
```

### Available Time Zones

Common time zones:

```yaml
---
# US Time Zones
$timezone = "America/New_York"    # EST/EDT
$timezone = "America/Chicago"      # CST/CDT
$timezone = "America/Los_Angeles"  # PST/PDT

# European Time Zones
$timezone = "Europe/London"        # GMT/BST
$timezone = "Europe/Paris"         # CET/CEST
$timezone = "Europe/Berlin"        # CET/CEST

# Asian Time Zones
$timezone = "Asia/Tokyo"           # JST
$timezone = "Asia/Shanghai"        # CST
$timezone = "Asia/Dubai"           # GST

# UTC
$timezone = "UTC"                  # Coordinated Universal Time
---
```

## Multiple Date Formats

Using different formats in the same document:

```yaml
---
$date_short = "DD/MM/YYYY"
$date_long = "DD MMMM, YYYY"
$datetime = "YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss"
---
```

**Short:** {$date_short}
**Long:** {$date_long}
**Full:** {$datetime}

## Date Calculations

### Relative Dates

Document age: {{ Math.floor(({$modified} - {$created}) / 86400) }} days

**Note:** This assumes date calculations are supported in your Zolt implementation.

### Example Usage

```yaml
---
$date_format = "DD MMMM YYYY"
---
```

# Project Documentation

**Created:** {$created}
**Last Modified:** {$modified}

:::if {$modified > {$created}}
*This document has been updated since creation.*
:::

## Metadata Integration

### Frontmatter with Dates

```yaml
---
title: "My Document"
created: {$created}
modified: {$modified}
date_format: "DD/MM/YYYY"
---
```

### Publishing Workflow

```yaml
---
title: "Blog Post"
published_at: {$created}
last_updated: {$modified}
status: "published"
---
```

## Date Display Patterns

### Human-Readable Dates

```yaml
---
$date_human = "MMMM DD, YYYY"
---
```

Today is {$date_human}

### Compact Dates

```yaml
---
$date_compact = "YYYYMMDD"
---
```

File: document_{$date_compact}.zlt

### Verbose Dates

```yaml
---
$date_verbose = "dddd, MMMM DD, YYYY 'at' HH:mm"
---
```

Full timestamp: {$date_verbose}

## Use Cases

### Document Templates

```yaml
---
title: "Meeting Minutes"
$date_format = "DD MMMM YYYY"
$meeting_date = {$created}
---
```

# Meeting Minutes - {$meeting_date}

**Date:** {$meeting_date}
**Time:** {$datetime_format}

### Version Control

```yaml
---
title: "Changelog"
$date_format = "YYYY-MM-DD"
---
```

## Changelog

### Version 1.0.0 ({$created})
- Initial release
- Core features implemented

### Version 1.1.0 ({$modified})
- Bug fixes
- Performance improvements

### Legal Documents

```yaml
---
title: "Terms of Service"
$date_format = "MMMM DD, YYYY"
$effective_date = {$created}
---
```

**Effective Date:** {$effective_date}

**Last Updated:** {$modified}

## Date Localization

### Multi-Language Support

```yaml
---
$lang = "fr"
$date_format = "DD/MM/YYYY"
---
```

**Date de création:** {$created}
**Dernière modification:** {$modified}

```yaml
---
$lang = "de"
$date_format = "DD.MM.YYYY"
---
```

**Erstellungsdatum:** {$created}
**Letzte Änderung:** {$modified}

## Dynamic Dates

### Publication Schedule

```yaml
---
$scheduled_date = "2026-03-01"
$date_format = "DD MMMM YYYY"
---
```

**Scheduled for:** {$scheduled_date}

### Expiration Date

```yaml
---
$expires = "2026-12-31"
$date_format = "DD MMMM YYYY"
---
```

**This document expires on:** {$expires}

## Best Practices

### Consistent Formatting

Use consistent date formats throughout a project:

```yaml
---
# Project-wide configuration
$date_format = "YYYY-MM-DD"
$datetime_format = "YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm"
$timezone = "UTC"
---
```

### Always Show Modified Date

```yaml
---
$date_format = "DD MMMM YYYY 'at' HH:mm"
---
```

**Created:** {$created}
**Last modified:** {$modified}

### Date Validation

```yaml
---
# Ensure dates are in the correct format
created: {$created}
modified: {$modified}
---
```

:::if {$modified < {$created}}
:::warning [Invalid Date]
Modified date is before creation date!
:::
:::

## Examples

### Software Release

```yaml
---
title: "Release Notes v2.0"
release_date: {$created}
date_format: "DD MMMM YYYY"
---
```

# Release Date: {$release_date}

This version was released on {$release_date}.

### Event Planning

```yaml
---
title: "Conference Schedule"
event_date: {$created}
date_format: "dddd, MMMM DD, YYYY"
---
```

**Event Date:** {$event_date}

### Academic Paper

```yaml
---
title: "Research Paper"
submission_date: {$created}
date_format: "YYYY-MM-DD"
---
```

